LONDON Tottenham announced the signing of Dutch international Steven Bergwijn from PSV Eindhoven for an undisclosed fee on Wednesday. "Steven has signed a contract with the club that will run until 2025 and will wear the number 23 shirt," said a statement from the Premier League club. With Harry Kane injured, Spurs manager Jose Mourinho was keen to bolster his attack during the January transfer window. More to follow...  